   <text type="translation">
      <body>
         <pb facs="1862_09_23_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Brunckow_Honkong_1.tif" n="envelope"/>
         <p>Messrs. L. Kniffler &amp; Co.<lb/> Nagasaki<lb/>⟨1862<lb/>Honkong 23rd Sept<lb/>C
                    Brunckow.<lb/>r[eceived]/7<del rend="overstrike">0</del>/10 62<lb/>a[nswered]
                15/12⟩</p>
         <pb facs="1862_09_23_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Brunckow_Honkong_2.tif" n="2"/>
         <p>Hongkong 23rd Sept 1862<lb/>Messrs. L. Kniffler + Co.<lb/>Nagasaki<lb/>I have the
                pleasure of acknowledging <lb/> receipt of your esteemed letter from 28th <lb/>
                Aug., with which you passed me the sales invoice<lb/>for 3 boxes of quinine + the
                remittance for this <lb/>$[?] 542.35 to Bourjau Hubener &amp; Co.,<lb/>which has
                been accepted.<lb/>The clearing of this consignment<lb/> is pleasing to me: that the
                article, as <lb/> I see <del rend="overstrike">furthermore</del> from your report
                from 8th Sep,<lb/>furthermore improved, could of course not have<lb/> been
                predicted. <lb/>I cannot help but notice, however,<lb/> that a remittance of the
                Provenirs[?]<lb/>to Shanghai, as I recommended to both <lb/> Mr. Gildemeister as
                well as you, would have been<lb/> 3-6% more profitable for me; you<lb/>noted
                Direct[?] in Shanghai 2½% and<lb/>the difference between the value of <lb/>Mex $ in
                Shanghai + the rate here would have <lb/>amounted to a further approx. 3%.<lb/>Your
                accounting procedures will<lb/> no doubt be in order, the $10,- received in
                surplus<lb/> I will pay to Mr. Lohe here, unless you write[?] more<lb/> about
                this.<lb/>Respectfully,<lb/>sincerely<lb/>E. Brunckow</p>
         <pb facs="1862_09_23_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Brunckow_Honkong_3.tif" n="3"/>
         <pb facs="1862_09_23_Kniffler_Nagasaki_von_Brunckow_Honkong_4.tif" n="4"/>
      </body>
   </text>
